		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.helpingwritersbecomeauthors.com/?p=8094</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[<p>Talk about wild and woolly! 2014 was a crazy busy, crazy awesome year. Not counting writing posts, some of my highlights included: A feature on NPR&#8217;s All Things Considered IPPY, NIEA, and Silver Falchion (Finalist) Awards for Structuring Your Novel NIEA Finalist mention for my portal fantasy Dreamlander Third Write to Done Top 10 Blogs for Writers Award 101 [&#8230;]</p>
<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.helpingwritersbecomeauthors.com/2014/12/top-writing-posts-2014.html">Top Writing Posts of 2014</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.helpingwritersbecomeauthors.com">Helping Writers Become Authors</a>.</p>
]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Talk about wild and woolly! 2014 was a crazy busy, crazy awesome year. Not counting writing posts, some of my highlights included:</p>
<ul>
<li>A feature on <a title="How to Kill a Character" href="http://www.npr.org/2014/04/05/298728897/how-to-kill-a-character" target="_blank">NPR&#8217;s <em>All Things Considered</em></a></li>
<li><a title="2014 Independent Publisher Book Awards Results" href="http://www.independentpublisher.com/article.php?page=1791" target="_blank">IPPY</a>, <a title="Winners of the 2014 NIEA Award" href="http://www.indieexcellence.com/indie-results-2014-winners.htm#120" target="_blank">NIEA</a>, and <a title="2014 Silver Falchion Award Winners and Finalists" href="http://www.killernashville.com/2014-silver-falchion-award-finalists/" target="_blank">Silver Falchion (Finalist)</a> Awards for <a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B00EJX08QA/ref=as_li_ss_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=390957&amp;creativeASIN=B00EJX08QA&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;tag=httpwwwkmweil-20" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><em>Structuring Your Novel</em></a></li>
<li><a title="2014 NIEA Finalists" href="http://www.indieexcellence.com/indie-results-2014-finalists.htm#45" target="_blank">NIEA Finalist</a> mention for my portal fantasy <a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B00A9WU99Q/ref=as_li_ss_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=390957&amp;creativeASIN=B00A9WU99Q&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;tag=httpwwwkmweil-20" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><em>Dreamlander</em></a></li>
<li>Third <a title="Top 10 Blogs for Writers 2013 – the Winners" href="http://writetodone.com/top-10-blogs-for-writers/" target="_blank"><em>Write to Done </em>Top 10 Blogs for Writers Award</a></li>
<li><a title="May/June 2014 Issues of Writer's Digest" href="http://www.writersdigestshop.com/writers-digest-may-june-2014-group" target="_blank">101 Best Websites for Writers </a>mention from <em>Writer&#8217;s Digest</em></li>
<li><a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B00LLOOSWA/ref=as_li_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=390957&amp;creativeASIN=B00LLOOSWA&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;tag=httpwwwkmweil-20&amp;linkId=BGHDQKS4PLPMLGHS" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><em>Jane Eyre: The Writer&#8217;s Digest Annotated Classic</em></a> release</li>
<li><a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B00P72KQI2/ref=as_li_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=390957&amp;creativeASIN=B00P72KQI2&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;tag=httpwwwkmweil-20&amp;linkId=CQ775LUWVNOE76Q3" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><em>Outlining Your Novel Workbook</em></a> and <a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B00P72KYWA/ref=as_li_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=390957&amp;creativeASIN=B00P72KYWA&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;tag=httpwwwkmweil-20&amp;linkId=EBB5EKWLI5TAO3U2" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><em>Structuring Your Novel</em> <em>Workbook</em></a> release</li>
<li><a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B00QHPSK3Q/ref=as_li_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=390957&amp;creativeASIN=B00QHPSK3Q&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;tag=httpwwwkmweil-20&amp;linkId=L2OY4R2XOTOBXCBC" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><em>Conquering Writer&#8217;s Block and Summoning Inspiration</em></a> release</li>
<li>Audio book releases for both <em><a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B00J9T9GSA/ref=as_li_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=390957&amp;creativeASIN=B00J9T9GSA&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;tag=httpwwwkmweil-20&amp;linkId=LWUMWDN5T2KXWYEL" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Outlining Your Novel</a> </em>and <a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B00R1UU6N8/ref=as_li_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=390957&amp;creativeASIN=B00R1UU6N8&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;tag=httpwwwkmweil-20&amp;linkId=YXRVGCLGHBTTMAZG" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><em>Structuring Your Novel</em></a></li>
<li>Two <a title="Workshops &amp; Webinars" href="http://www.helpingwritersbecomeauthors.com/resources/workshops-webinars" target="_blank">webinars</a> for <em>Writer&#8217;s Digest</em> and one for ACFW</li>
<li>Japanese translation of <em>Structuring Your Novel</em> and Korean translation of <em>Outlining Your Novel</em></li>
<li>Two articles in the <em>Writer&#8217;s Digest</em> magazine</li>
<li>And, oh yeah, a mention on actor Robert Downey, Jr.&#8217;s Facebook page!</li>
</ul>
<p>And on the personal front, there was that entirely awesome jaunt to Hawaii.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.helpingwritersbecomeauthors.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/IMG_9261.jpg"><img class="  wp-image-8256 aligncenter" src="http://www.helpingwritersbecomeauthors.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/IMG_9261.jpg" alt="K.M. Weiland in Hawaii" width="571" height="428" /></a></p>
<p>As always, I am humbled by the enthusiasm of Wordplayers everywhere! And I&#8217;m thrilled and fulfilled to be able to help you out on your writing journeys. Here&#8217;s to an even wilder 2015! And, to get you started, take a look at <em>Helping Writers Become Authors&#8217;</em> Top 10 Writing Posts of 2014&#8211;based on page rank&#8211;just in case you missed them or want to brush up.</p>
<h2>Top Writing Posts on <em>Helping Writers Become Authors</em> in 2014</h2>
<p><strong>1.</strong> <a title="Creating Stunning Character Arcs, Pt. 1: Can You Structure Characters?" href="http://www.helpingwritersbecomeauthors.com/2014/02/character-arcs-1.html" target="_blank">Creating Stunning Character Arcs</a></p>
<p><strong>2.</strong> <a title="How to Successfully Kill a Character: The Checklist" href="http://www.helpingwritersbecomeauthors.com/2014/01/kill-a-character.html" target="_blank">How to Successfully Kill a Character: The Checklist</a></p>
<p><strong>3.</strong> <a title="Why Your Character’s Goal Needs to Be 1 of These 5 Things" href="http://www.helpingwritersbecomeauthors.com/2014/10/characters-goal.html" target="_blank">Why Your Character’s Goal Needs to Be 1 of These 5 Things</a></p>
<p><strong>4. </strong><a title="Make Your Character Reactions Twice as Interesting" href="http://www.helpingwritersbecomeauthors.com/2014/05/character-reactions.html" target="_blank">Make Your Character Reactions Twice as Interesting</a></p>
