<p>And what about 2015? For the most part, 2015 seems to be shaping up to be the Year of the Novel for me. My two major projects will be finishing up edits on my historical dieselpunk story <em><a title="Storming" href="http://www.kmweiland.com/about-k-m-weiland/#storming" target="_blank">Storming</a> </em>to get it ready for publication in late fall or early winter and writing the first draft of my historical superhero story <a title="Wayfarer" href="http://www.kmweiland.com/about-k-m-weiland/#wayfarer" target="_blank"><em>Wayfarer</em></a>.</p>
<p>Since 2014 was (as you can see) primarily focused on non-novel stuff, I’m dancing all over with the chance to immerse myself in fictional worlds once again. However, I’m also hoping to work on a handful of writing how-to projects for you all as well. My big goal is to finish a couple of courses, one based on <em>Outlining Your Novel</em> and one on <em>Structuring Your Novel</em>. I also have a <a title="Most Common Writing Mistakes Series" href="http://www.helpingwritersbecomeauthors.com/category/most-common-writing-mistakes" target="_blank">Most Common Writing Mistakes</a> book waiting in the wings. It’s going to be a fun year!</p>
